#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Names.phtml:28
msgid ""
"Each arc on the circumference is one of the top surnames in the tree, ranked "
"by how many marriages that surname appears in (as husband OR wife). Ribbons "
"between two arcs encode the number of marriages between those surnames; "
"thickness is proportional to that count. The diagram is symmetric — a "
"Schmidt × Müller marriage contributes equally to both arcs. Self-loops on an "
"arc represent endogamous marriages where husband and wife share a surname."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Names.phtml:22
msgid ""
"Each band stands for one of the most common given names in the tree. The "
"band's vertical thickness in a given decade shows how many individuals born "
"in that decade carried that name. The silhouette layout centres each band "
"around zero, so the chart reads as relative magnitudes — hover any band to "
"see absolute counts and its peak decade."
msgstr ""
"Hvert bånd står for ett av de vanligste fornavnene i stamtreet. Båndets "
"vertikale tykkelse i et gitt tiår viser hvor mange personer født i det "
"tiåret som bar det navnet. Silhuett-oppsettet sentrerer hvert bånd rundt "
"null, så diagrammet leses som relative størrelser — hold musen over et bånd "
"for å se absolutte tall og toppiåret."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Family.phtml:422
msgid ""
"Each bar is one century of recorded divorces. The segments split the bar "
"into five life-stage age bands measured at the time of divorce (0–24, 25–34, "
"35–44, 45–54, 55+) plus an Unknown band for divorces with no usable birth "
"date on either spouse. One tick per divorce, classified by the husband's age "
"when present and the wife's age otherwise, so the per-century totals line up "
"exactly with the divorces-by-century chart above. Hover any segment for the "
"per-band count and the century total."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Family.phtml:560
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Each bar is one decade, normalised to 100 %% — the four segments stack 1, 2, "
"3, and 4 or more children per family. Surfaces the shift from large to small "
"families over time."
msgstr ""
"Hver søyle er ett tiår, normalisert til 100 %% — de fire segmentene stabler "
"1, 2, 3 og 4 eller flere barn per familie. Viser skiftet fra store til små "
"familier over tid."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Places.phtml:22
msgid ""
"Each flow shows individuals who were born in one country and died in "
"another. The flow's thickness encodes the count: thicker bands mean more "
"migrations along that path. Same-country trajectories are excluded — they're "
"not migration. Hover any band to see the exact source → destination and "
"individual count."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Family.phtml:82
msgid ""
"Each person in the tree has up to 30 possible direct ancestors within four "
"generations (2 parents + 4 grandparents + 8 great-grandparents + 16 great-"
"great-grandparents). The pedigree-completeness index (Lacy 1989) is the "
"fraction of those 30 slots that are actually documented for that individual. "
"The number shown here is the average across every individual in the tree, so "
"12 percent means \"on average each person has 12 percent of their 4-"
"generation ancestry recorded\". Higher = more thorough research; lower = "
"many gaps. Caveats: pedigree-collapse duplicates (cousin marriages) are not "
"deduplicated, recent leaf-imports without ancestors drag the average down, "
"and only direct ancestors are counted — siblings / cousins are out of scope."
msgstr ""
"Hver person i stamtreet har opptil 30 mulige direkte forfedre i fire "
"generasjoner. Stamtreskompletteringsindeksen (Lacy 1989) er andelen av disse "
"plassene som faktisk er dokumentert. Høyere = grundigere forskning; lavere = "
"mange hull."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Family.phtml:787
msgid ""
"Each step is one parent–child link upward; siblings, half-lines and dead-"
"ends are merged into the longest path."
msgstr ""
"Hvert trinn er én forelder–barn-lenke oppover; søsken, halvlinjer og "
"blindgater slås sammen i den lengste stien."

